    "body": "This does fix some behaviors, but there are still some others that remain:\n- Clicking on save in the toolbar causes a jump because of the `ensure_focus` logic that appears in a few places. Let's try removing that stuff as well (it is super simple and only in a few places).\n- Hitting `esc` to enter command mode can cause a jump if the cell is large and not scrolled into the optimal position. The code that does this is carefully commented by me, but I thought that code behaved differently than it does now. It could be a browser change or my memory. @jdfreder do you remember how this behaved in 2.0?\n- There are still 2 calls to `focus_cell` in `maintoolbar.js` to manage the cell type and celltoolbar select menues. I am not sure how these will behave after we re-add those to the register_events...\n"
  },
