    "body": ">  let's do add the cell type and celltoolbar select to register_events \n\ndone\n\n> Clicking on save in the toolbar causes a jump \n\nfixed\n\n> There are still 2 calls to focus_cell in maintoolbar.js\n\nI think these should stay. The behavior when focus is not sent back to the notebook when a cell is changed seems surprising, because you are operating on an element that isn't focused, and you can't get back to the notebook without clicking somewhere after making the change.\n\n2.x doesn't have register_events and doesn't focus the cell, which means the behavior is mostly the same as register_events + focus, except the select element remains highlighted, even though it won't actually receive keyboard events. I think register_events + focus is an improvement over the 2.x behavior.\n\n> Hitting esc to enter command mode can cause a jump\n\nFrom testing, it appears that 2.x has the same behavior on this as 3.0, so I don't think it's a regression.\n\nReading the comment, we are calling `focus_cell()` in order to trigger CM.blur, which in turn triggers command mode. I've updated the PR to blur CM directly, which seems to work, and avoids the focus call. This is the change that makes me most squeamish about backporting.\n"
  },
